:''For punch card sorting machines, see [[IBM 80 series Card Sorters]].''

A '''cash sorter machine''' is a [[machine]] used for sorting [[banknotes]]. Cash Sorters can file through a number of banknotes, and sort it into [[Denomination (currency)|denominations.]] Many Cash Sorters also function as a [[banknote counter]], and can count money as well as splitting them into groups. Some cash sorters can also detect [[counterfeit money]] using security features of the banknote. Primary users are [[bank]]s, [[financial institution]]s, [[casino]]s, and large [[theme park]]s, as they all come across large amounts of [[cash]].

